,Not Recommended,246090,28737993,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,disco,"DO NOT BUY THIS GAME FOR ANY MONEY. Just read all the reviews others have given it.This game, given another year in development, could have been good. But the alpha version you get here is really frustrating to play:- Only one saved game at a time, and auto save only. So if anything goes wrong, that's all your time wasted.- Quite often when raiding a derelict (which should be a fun thing to do), oxygen levels will drop for no reason and kill all your guys.- A single raider can easily kill way too many of your experienced guys. Even in areas that are meant to have low threat levels and even when your guys are firing back (and because of AI bugs, sometimes they don't).- I've not noticed any difference in the threat level of the main map, because I can get raided once in an hour in a high area, and almost once a minute in a low area. It makes no sense and feels like the map rating wasn't connected to anything.- The AI has serious flaws, the most irritating of which is where your security team WILL JUST STAND there and get killed. Even 10 highly trained guys will stand right next to a raider and let themselves all be killed. There is also a bug where they get confused and refused to enter the base to regain oxygen, eventually dying.- You can't tell your guys to leave an area, which means that once you own a derelict it becomes a magnate for guys and raiders which is no end of trouble. For instance, When raiders retake a derelict, technicians and doctors will all float over and get killed. I know an emergency switch is used for this, but derelicts don't come with any.- You can't pan when in the building menu, which means you have to start all over again if the camera isn't perfect.- You can view oxygen levels, but not power levels, and is seems power units need to be close enough to power things. So you have to guess where power is going.- Oxygen leaks are impossible to spot sometimes if a ****ing raider blows out a wall that's not in an obvious spot. The O2 overlay needs to show leak spots.- Sometime when building a new base, oxygen recyclers don't work.There's enough game here that would be worth checking out if it were free. BUT, because this isn't on early access I can't recommend spending any money on it. There's just WAY too many game breaking flaws that end up ruining your time.The fact Double Fine thought it was OK to continue to charge money for such a broken game, and with no plans to fix any of it, they get a BIG F.U from me. Seriously, I would never trust anything from them ever again (especially their kick starters)."
