cide that they absolutely need to do floor pushups right in your airlock door, and then everybody will suffocate to death.These things are quite forgivable in an alpha game. Frustrating, but understandable. It's alpha, I get it. Things might be broken or unfinished. I'm fine with that. But if ANY of this crap manages to slip into the 1.0 release? That's just garbage.(Edit: Apparently The S-Word is too raunchy for a review. Sigh.)----1.01 UpdateIt has improved nothing at all.No. I absolutely do not recommend. It continues to justnot work. I started two bases today after the 1.01 patch, the one designed to ""finish"" the game. I see no significant improvements. Build orders are randomly followed, regardless of importance. Citizens start ""running away"" for no obvious reason. Random station boarding parties still utterly annihilate you base regardless of the number of security personnell you have assigned. Security teams clearing derelicts still seem to think that actually shooting the hostiles is a silly concept.But hey, at least now there's a tutorial! A rather unnecessary one, since the game mechanics are not at all complicated, and I felt were very obviously conveyed through normal play. The problem isn't the players misunderstanding the game mechanics - it's that the game simplydoesn't f-ing work.----FinalFinal recommendation:DO NOT PURCHASE THIS. EVER.Secondary recommendation:Never trust DoubleFine again. Only buy a product once it has been actually released, and you've tried it, and it actually works, and the community is being treated well. Do not give support (either financial or social) to companies that make bad decisions. And especially not companies that make bad decisions, then try to tell you how great their decisions actually were."
