,Not Recommended,246090,12142694,"Posted: 18 September, 2014",all,[ANGRYMAN],"This game will never-ever be worth the full price now that DF have announced that they're abandoning development. It MIGHT be worth a quater of the price IF the community gets into modding it to fix serious issues and add much needed content.MIGHTIF---I guess i should update this review now that the game has been released and has been updated to 1.05.I still play this game, and at the time of the edit to this review, i've invested about 70 hours into countless new games.The updates have helped a whole lot, but the game still has some playability issues:Doctors will often ignore corpses, which leads to bad morale, which leads to violence which leads to drastic crew loss.Raider events are too randomised, and can often lead to base failure in the very early game, or general drastic crew loss.The added raider mega-fleet event is a good idea in principal, but is vastly over-powered.Construction crew often take huge detors to the next block to be built when in space, which can lead to a new base failing, or causing unrecoverable crew loss in the very early game.Even with my reasonable system spec and the relative simplicity of the game, it tends to lag-out far too much.Generally; Base failure seems to be down to chance rather than skill.There are positives, howeverThere are mods appearing now, which is great. The community is addressing balence issues and adding reaseatch and similar.Workshop support is still very much missing, sadly.Overall:Has the potential to be a reasonable casual game, but really isn't worth the full price at all. Perhaps at a quater the price, it woulnd't be so bad."
