,Not Recommended,246090,12048275,"Posted: 10 September, 2014",all,Baer,"This is a potentially really good game. It does have the feeling of the old ""Theme XYZ"" games, and it has an overal oldschool feel, which is greatly appreciated.The graphics are neat, gameplay is potentially superb and endless, there even is some subtle, underlying humour which makes life in space more tolerable. The audio is also fairly standard, but fitting and nice.Unfortunately, at this early stage of development, the game is nigh unplayable. The AI is just, well, close to non-existant. ""Events"" are a tad too catastrophic and can easily lead to total failure (usually because AI doesn't do what it's supposed to, though). There is very little control over the space station's inhabitants' actions, there is no way to prioritize tasks. Occasional bugs will result in a lot of citizens dying for random reasons (eg, can't open a perfectly functioning door, or they won't come back from space when low on oxygen, and so on), whose corpses nobody will remove (again, AI failure). I'd say the AI  is what really needs some tweaking, right now.All in all, the game has a very nice backbone and quite some flesh, along with a few interesting quirks, but needs a lot (A LOT) of polishing yet. I recommend you try this game with this in mind."
,Not Recommended,246090,12015013,"Posted: 7 September, 2014",all,Edelweiß,"First let me say this: I have a very deep love for Dwarf Fortress. I absolutely adore that game so I have bought almost every dwarf fortressesque game on early access.However, this game: Spacebase DF-9 is not a good game. Why? Several reasons, but most relate to really bad controls. To build stuff or select or anything is really fiddily because it has a hard time registrating where the mouse is pointing on the grid - so you have a really hard game just controlling the damn game. Also the UI is hard to understand sometimes. The citizens all have their own individual ""twitter feeds"" where they write what the think of your space station, but the problem is that it's hard to understand exactly what their problems are. The game is also very unbalanced so it's hard to get a space base running and the nature of space means that it's important to make sure that you build correctly the first time. More so than in dwarf fortress where you can occasionally correct mistakes or convert rooms. Here your items often take more than 1 space on a grid so you'll find that its harder to convert rooms to other things. Also the rooms needs to be substantially bigger and you cannot put stuff like beds beside walls because they need all of the bed's adjacent squares to be free.EDIT: It has been a long time since the developers decided to abandon this project. I think I speak for all of us who bought this game when I say that we're all deeply disappointed in them. We all think it's a scam, and that it was not finished like it should have been. They never fixed the interface or the controlling problems. Stay away from this scam if  you  know what's good for you."
