,Not Recommended,246090,11996265,"Posted: 6 September, 2014",all,Etheras,"I used to like this game. Post version 6 release, it now totally sucks.Why?Specifically the AI doesn't seem capable of managing the new functionality. Also the threat system is totally broken. For some reason in my ""extreme low"" hostility sector I get constant pirate raids (and I do mean constant. Like... 30 seconds after beating the last one there's another).  Or a meteor impact. The ""game"" (if one can call it that anymore) has gone from a space colony sim to a constant crisis.But more fundamentally... the brig system doesn't work right, nor the tantrum system. So first the brig system: enemies can often get ""subdued"" where they just stand there endlessly until they starve. If you have a brig, you can store them there instead. There doesn't appear to be any reason to do this that I can see. There is no benefit. Its preferable to let enemies starve, especially because sometimes captured enemies lose their ""subdued"" flag and simply walk out of the brig to shoot up your base again. Seriously... WHAT IS THE POINT? Also... did you guys even test this release?? Its almost entirely unplayable.Okay so now to the tantrum system. Colonists can get freaked out, wreck the place up, and fight with fellow colonists. Yet for some reason this happens to happy colonists sometimes. I suppose one could say they ""just snap"" or something but... once again, what is the point of happiness if it doesn't do anything? Bigger problem is after a tantrumed colonist is subdued they lay there and nothing happens. Even if you have doctors on staff, they don't seem to treat the person like... laying there in the hallway injured. It appears that the primary role of doctors is simply corpse disposal, rather than anything doctor-y.If steam had a numeric rating system, I'd give this 1 of 5 stars. Its really abysmal and should never have been released with the numerous game-breaking bugs. At least it was playable before."
