,Not Recommended,246090,11992921,"Posted: 5 September, 2014",all,biochimera,"So the producers decided to just go ""Eh, close enough, release it, move on"". Shame that is simply isn't done at all. I leave my original early access review below, but the character AI is still atrocious, there is no way to prioritize building, the security is still slow to respond to threats, the characters are just too dumb to live (Hey, this robot killed this guy, so I'll just go over and grab his body while the robot is still around), it is finicky to find a starting spot as there is no rhyme or reason to the colony select screen, the tutorial doesn't tell you jack, the construction controls are non-intuitive, you can't rotate the screen so placement of some objects is difficult, the builders build things in a random fashion (see point about prioritizing above), the aliens are only different in appearance, no trading available with ships, I could go on and on. I was hoping for a better version of Startopia, but this game is nowhere near that level. Indeed, it still plays pretty much like an alpha, and can not seriously be considered a finished game. Especially a game with no on-going support. Do not buy.________________________________________________________________________________Spacebase DF-9 is a very very alpha game. The AI just simply is broken. Having your characters die because they are all standing around in one room instead of doing tasks is not fun at all, and watching one lone raider knock out/off half your station plus all your oxygen recyclers with no security moving to do jack about it is just infuriating. Add in very dumb things like your crew deciding the airlock is a great place to hang out, and yeah, needs much more work before it's in a state worthy to play."
