,Recommended,246090,23886235,"Posted: 28 June, 2016",all,Cromulons,"I'm sure everyone knows this, but I must include it on my review. This game has been abandoned by the developers.The developers are also expecting modders to finish the game for them...but didn't make a workshop compatability...*facepalm*. Seriously devs? so at the moment, there are very few mods out there and they are scattered all over the internet, and google search is no help.However, there is a new mod called ""unoffical patch"" to fix some bugs and add some features. I recommend you download that mod or be greeted with bugs apocalypse.Now lets talk gameplay.I don't know what they normally call them, settlers? austronaut? pawn? I'll just name it ""people"".Unfortunately, you can't move your people, which can be very annoying when raiders are on sight.You can assign them up to 9 jobs, some people are more skilled on certain job and also enjoy/hate certain job.The jobs are;Builder: self explanatoryTechnician: maintain and fixes objectsMiner: self explanatorySecurity: shoot hostile enemy, and follow security beacon that you can set.Bartender: Tends the bar which increase happiness.Botanist: tends the garden.Scientist: Make researches to unlock things.Doctor: Heal and cure diseases/illnessJanitor: Clean corpsesUnassigned: defaultPeople have needs, and they can go up and down shown on a graph. I don't know what most of these does to the person.Duty, Social, Morale, Stuff, Energy, Hunger, Fun. Those are the 7 needs of a person.People also have ""thoughts"" that you can read. Some of them are about friends and enemy they made, an object they built, or even a certain doom they are about to encounter. Thoughts really define them and I enjoy pausing the game and reading them.They also have a nice hand drawn avatar so you know what they look like and perks, if they have low self esteem or they are anxious, etc.Each person really is different from the rest and it's amazing how much detail they have. It's ashamed this game is abandoned.Now let's talk about building.There are 13 rooms you can build, and they are;Airlock: In and out of the space stationLife Support: For placing Oxygen machineReactor: for powering the entire space stationRefinery: smelting rocks into matter (money)Residence: Build beds to increase population limitPub: increase happinessGarden: Grow foodFitness: gymResearch: build research table for scientistInfirmary: HospitalBrig: prisonCommand: Threat monitoringUnzoned: plain old roomEach of these rooms have certain objects that can only be placed on that room. All objects (and wall/floor) cost matter to build.Matter can be obtained by mining rocks and smelting it on a refinery machine.To build a room, you need to inclosed it with walls and floors. If a wall or a floor is destroyed, and a person is in that room, they will be sucked into the vacume of space and die.Walls/floors and objects can be destroyed from astroids and raiders.There are random encounter in the game.There are people that you can communicate with that randomly pops up (when they are near you).If you respond to their message, then you can either gain a person or be targeted by raiders.This is the risk you need to think about before accepting their calls.There are also an actual spaceship that shows in your game. You can either send your security (via security beacon) or leave it alone until it leaves the game.Spacebase DF9 had potentials, but its been abandon before it can even fly. I really wish someone would make a similar game. SOMEONE PLEASE!That being said, would I recommend this game? Not on full price. Buy this game when it's 90% on sale."
