,Not Recommended,246090,8201782,"Posted: 22 December, 2013",all,Niiyo-chan,"The game seems like it has potential, but it simply isn't even close to being there yet. Releasing it to the public in this state was a mistake. Everything feels extremely barebones, and I've encountered numerous bugs that forced me to start over (such as people getting stuck in an airlock). There's even a room type that does absolutely nothing (why even add it in yet?). I'm assuming said room will, in the future, function as a power plant for your station, but at the moment it's purely for decoration.The character relationships aren't close to being where they should be, and it doesn't seem like there's any reason to build separate quarters for each character over one communal bedroom. I was looking forward to the inhabitants becoming friends, getting married, having kids, etc. At the moment it seems the only relationship types are ""friend"" and ""enemy"".The random events seem limited to a debris pummeling your station, raiders arriving, and new recruits arriving. Debris is easily dealt with by installing a fire extinguisher in each room, raiders will leave if asked, and new recruits offer to stay no matter how poorly you're running your station.I bought this game expecting to build my very own Babylon 5 or Deep Space 9, but it simply isn't anywhere close to being there yet. I'm very much looking forward to new features and improvements, but at the moment I cannot recommend this game. I do think that will change in the future if the game lives up to the potential of its concept.Edit: Since I wrote this, Double Fine has announced that they're leaving this game an unfinished mess. Stay away. Far away. And boycott Double Fine."
