,Not Recommended,246090,8436505,"Posted: 30 December, 2013",all,OmegaJeff,"There's something very engaging about this little base building sim.  The character of your citizens, the flavor of the room types and furnishings, the banter with incoming vessels.Bugginess aside, the game is still very incomplete.  It serves to give you a taste of what the finished game will be, but it wont satisfy.  For Alpha 3 though, it's in a pretty good place.But even ignoring it's alpha state, there are some issues with the design I find a bit lacking.  Issues I'm not sure will be resolved by the official launch.  For instance, there is no vertical building.  Your citizens can space walk in 3D, but you can only build in 2D.  There is also only one material to mine and build with.  Some of the other issues I could list off are relatively minor, or things that they're likely to address for RC.  But these two core design points are things that fundumentally narrow the experience, and it's not clear if they'll be resolved.Ultimatley I say wait, unless you want this sitting in your library and eyeing you until it's finished (and I'll probably update my review at that point just to be fair),"
