,Not Recommended,246090,20059881,"Posted: 28 December, 2015",all,Kunovega,"In its current form the game is worth less than $1Unfortunately it may never be improved beyond that state. If you want to buy it for $1 (on sale) and hope that several years from now the playerbase mod team actually turns this into a working game, go for it.But don't say you weren't warned. I bought this for a $1 knowing what I was getting into and I can't say I'm disapointed simply because I wanted to poke around and see what all the negative hype has been about. And the reality is, this game can not be recommended with a good consience.All the potential for a good game is here and than you realize your content ends shortly after figuring out how the controls work. There's no campaign, the tutorial is laughably poor at even explaining the basics and the sandbox play (which is pretty much all that exists) is laughably short before it becomes an endless loop.You start with a random team of 3 with random skills in a random zone of space with random resources and (almost) random difficulty. You have some minor influence over how to skew the randomness (by choosing different zones of space); but in the end the only real choice you have is:pick a dangerous area or pick a non dangerous area (or rather: pick an area where you cant play because you die instantly or pick an area where nothing happens until later and than goes into an endless loop of the same easily defeated enemies)I don't know, I had some silly fun poking around with it for about an hour but there's just not much here and while I applaud the playerbase mod team for making an effort at improving the game I know full well that it could take years before there's enough fixes and content additions to make this game playable.I'll probably replay it for a few minutes every year or so just to see if they ever do anything with it.Edit: And I fell asleep listening to the music while playing, which is the only reason it looks like I have some hours of play time. Content was over in less than an hour. The rest of the listed play time was watching the spacebase like a fishbowl or sleeping with the music from the game playing."
