,Recommended,246090,14502735,"Posted: 16 February, 2015",all,jessictia,"After glancing at the review page for this game, I feel obligated to share my experiences with this game.Some of the positives:*You have to actually plan a base and monitor your resources in order to survive*Every play through is different.*You choose what type of game you plan on embarking on from the very start.- Do you want a lot of hostiles?- Do you want to build your base close to a warp gate so you will have visitors (Friendly & hostile?)- Stellar Density: Do you want to have an abundance of ""money"" or do you want to have to really work for it?Some of the negatives:*Yes, the game is no longer being developed*Yes, there are many things not completed-The game is still very much playable*Yes, there are many features that should have been added in, via the Dev’s constant updates, such as:-Multi-level base construction-Teleporters-holodecksThis game started out as an early access game and unfortunately it also ended that way.  The way I see it, anyone on steam, including myself, takes a chance when buying a game that is in early access.  Will it be phenomenal? Will it suck? When will development finish? Will it ever finish? Will this new bug fix crash the entire game?The game may not be 100% complete, but at least Double Fine released the source code to their fans to continue development.  Sometimes, it's the fans that understand the game on a much deeper level than the developers ever could.With that being said, should you purchase this game at $20?In short...NO WAY!!  Should you never play this game though? NO!!! Wait for it to go on sale and purchase once the price drops to a good amount.  You can get HOURS AND HOURS of play time out of this game - and isn't that what you want from any game you decide to sit down and play?!?!"
