76561198006623804,Recommended,246090,11192200,"Posted: 11 July, 2014",all,Ogrup,"[EDIT] I wrote this review when I assumed (hoped!) funding would continue and the game would reach its promising potential. With version 1.0 on the way and a general air of abandonment from DF, I'm less keen to recommend this. I still load it up now and again and lament the missed opportunity...================I'm offering up a cautious recommendation here. This game is very promising, while still being far from a complete experience in its current state (Alpha 5d). I bought it on the strength of it being made by Double Fine, who I think have a habit of putting out some really fun games. The recommendation is partially based on their reputation.As other reviewers have mentioned, the UI is great and the overall aesthetic brings to mind 70s/ 80s SF such as Hitchhikers Guide to the Galaxy or Dark Star. Having said that, the devs should really set about implementing some goal-based gameplay soon enough. It seems an odd move to put it out in its current state since there's not the level of freedom for it to act simply as a light space survival sim. There isn't really enough depth at the moment for the player to come up with their own objectives beyond not dying for long enough to build a space-pub. In its current state it looks like you can try out all the space- decor and experience the space- mining and space- pirates in a fairly short stretch of time. Basically, I love the content so far and I'd like there to be more.I really hope there is continued support and funding on this project. There have been a few negative reviews on Steam but most people acknowledge the potential here. I look forward to seeing the updates and in the meantime, I can set about building my Silent Running style interstellar greenhouse."
