,Recommended,246090,9482759,"Posted: 14 March, 2014",all,Hoi! Oi!,"Developers at Double Fine are consistently updating the game because it IS an Early Access/Beta. I am glad I got SpaceBase DF-9 on sale for about ten bucks, but it is definitely not worth twenty. I suggest waiting for it to go on sale if you want to try it out.In SpaceBase DF-9, there's no micro-managing. The A.I. take on a life of their own once you give them a task so it can get rather frustrating. And most of them are very, very moody, which affect their work ethic severely (ugh). They're fairly stupid at their current stage of development, so you can expect to lose a base very quickly - regardless of whether you're playing the game correctly or not. And if your base doesn't fall apart right away, it will eventually. It takes quite a while to understand how each A.I. functions (due to their personalities) and how to work around them.Even with all that said, it's a very fun game. I have fun, anyway. It helps that I enjoy simulator games. It's space sims! Sorta."
