,Recommended,246090,10992843,"Posted: 30 June, 2014",all,James,"I've been playing the alpha 5b (Doctors with Boarders) build, and the game definitely has promise.Not everything works yet (e.g. power reactors don't seem to serve a purpose), and some things work when they probably shouldn't (e.g. the wall mounted turrets inside the base seem to be able to shoot raider ships that are outside).  The game also currently lacks any tutorial content, so you'll need to learn by playing or look for outside information.  There is enough there to enjoy, although after a few hours you'll probably reach the end of what's available and need to restart keep it from getting boring.There is minimal micro-management options available in the game (you can assign jobs to people and tell them to go to the infirmary), so you need to be careful how much work you queue up since there is no way to prioritise it.  There are other mechanics that don't work so well, such as sending security personel to derelict bases to investigate: the bases always seemed to be hostile and I would end up with some of my people dying.  I found it easier to deal with these bases by getting a builder to knock holes in a few walls to vent the atmosphere first.You can already see some of the humour that Double Fine is known for.  Each person has a SpaceFace feed where they make notes about their day.  There is humour in some of the game mechanics, such as doctors getting rid of the dead bodies in the same matter refineries used by the miners.It'll be interesting to see how the game develops."
