76561198325245237,Recommended,246090,28662138,"Posted: 25 December, 2016",all,menubar,"This game gets an 8/10 from me. It's a really relaxing game when taken for what it is. I am reviewing it as version 1.06 Mac OSX no mods installed. I had a free version for months before finding it on steam for 99¢ and just had to buy it to encourage the developers just a little bit with my tiny contribution. I would easily pay $5 bucks for it.You're basically thrown into space, given 3 guys and very little resources to start building your space base. In the beginning you need to start as small as possible, building just the bare necessities. Once you have a small (3x3) airlock room, another room just large enough to hold 3 oxygen recyclers, and a room just large enough for a matter refinery, the rest is a piece of cake.The game is 90% relaxing, mining and building, welcoming new (weird & silly) inhabitants, and pretty much trying to keep everyone fed, breathing, and happy - or as happy as one can be in a fragile domicile in space. You need to begin early considering how to protect your base from bad guys that pop in periodically, and asteroid impact damages.Aside from the few (easy) dangers, it's just a relaxing sandbox style building game where you can be creative in making a space base to be proud of. The interface is pretty much well organized, which is an aspect that many games like this get wrong. I enjoy the weird types of characters/aliens and their thoughts and interactions.Many people complain about the AI being ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥, but you have to pay attention to what each character is good or bad at and by what degree they would suck at a job. You have to assign them to duties they are good at and actually enjoy doing. Some are good at a job, but hate doing it, so yeah, they'll stand around playing games on their pads instead of doing any work, unless you assign them to a duty they enjoy. I find this aspect completely adorable, as it really adds to the immersion and how you feel or care for each individual. I also love the names - imagining how an alien would pronounce his name written as ""Uneekly (nicely)"" - that sorta thing.It's currently (for the past several months) been my favorite game for when I just want to relax and make a creative little space base. The few, easy dangers add just enough of that random aspect to keep you on your toes and influence the shape and direction your base takes. Have lots of good tech guys and your base will run smoothly - put lotsa gun turrets all around the outside walls and you'll be safe enough to survive a large attack that eventually happens. And just have fun building and watching how your inhabitants get along.My only complaint is - once you get a VERY LARGE base, things go bad fast. Machines start failing, catching on fire, destroying themselves everywhere, no matter how many techs you have to fix them. But I guess this is just a sign that I've gone way too far with this base and should just start a new one, haha.Lotsa people be hatin' on it, but it's been one of my favorite, relaxing games that I keep going back to."
,Recommended,246090,13465291,"Posted: 19 December, 2014",all,Махiматоя,"Meh meh meh, meh meh meh. That's what almost every negative review here sounds like. All they talk about is how double fine abandoned spacebase DF-9 (which is true, but that doesn't really qualify as a reason for bad reviews.). Honestly, the gameplay here is a bit glitchy (a doctor carries away a dead body but still shows corpse, etc.), but I myself enjoyed this game (until I moved on to other games), mostly because It looked somewhat like prison architect, but less just spamming the HIRE A GUARD! button (not that I own that game, but I have played once or twice, and thats where a lot of my time went) and more problems to take care of. Now, onto the gameplay besides the prison architect style building stuff. 1: more controlled problems. In pris. arch., all you really need to worry about is food. Here you have emotions, job liking, oxygen, sleep, and nothing more that I can remember. 2: uncontrollable problems: in prison arch., you have riots. Here, you have brawls, meteor strikes, fires, betrayals, parasites and raiders. nuf' said. I like this game, so I hope you read this actually sensible review, and buy spacebase DF-9."
