,Not Recommended,246090,8453092,"Posted: 31 December, 2013",all,재재,"I was hesitant at first with all the alpha games on steam. The game is great, a blast to play and pleasnt to learn. The soundtrack is enchating as space scenes are. You start with 3 characters you can only lightly influence. Each one can be assigned a task within the spacebase, they are: botanist, bartender, builder, technician, security, miner. (Botanist grow food for the bartender to serve in a pub, the others shouldn't need explanation). Each person can perform each task at a level granted by skill. So it allows an opportunity to manage your labor resources as well as material resources. After while you will slowly build a  base of up to 100 or so people if you can survive impacting debris and pirate raiders. Opportunities to plunder derelict ships will give you bonus space or resources. While definently a playable alpha build, you can probably do just about everything in eight hours, more content would make replay value more substantial. Overall impressive game, can't wait for the finished build. *Edit I have to change my opinion to negative because the game was published seemingly before it was finished."
